745
00:51:23,915 --> 00:51:25,834
Take off these glasses.

746
00:51:29,504 --> 00:51:31,798
You have nice eyes, you know?

747
00:51:33,633 --> 00:51:35,427
Do me another favor?

748
00:51:36,428 --> 00:51:38,805
Why don't you take off that hat?

749
00:51:45,103 --> 00:51:47,355
I always knew you was pretty.

750
00:51:48,857 --> 00:51:51,526
- Don't tease me.
- I'm not teasing you.

751
00:51:54,863 --> 00:51:56,698
I ain't teasing you.

752
00:51:57,741 --> 00:52:00,368
I just wanna...
I wanna kiss you.

753
00:52:03,038 --> 00:52:06,041
You don't have to kiss me back
if you don't wanna,

754
00:52:06,124 --> 00:52:07,959
but I wanna kiss you.

755
00:53:20,282 --> 00:53:23,410
- Heard you had a fight coming up.
- Next month.

756
00:53:23,451 --> 00:53:25,245
January 27, right?

757
00:53:25,287 --> 00:53:27,289
That's good. Come down to the gym.

758
00:53:27,330 --> 00:53:29,624
We'll get you in shape.
How's your weight?

759
00:53:29,708 --> 00:53:32,586
- 175.
- Hey, Rock. How you doing?

760
00:53:32,627 --> 00:53:34,838
Mick was looking for
you up there, man.

761
00:53:34,921 --> 00:53:37,132
- For me? You're sure?
- Yeah, yeah.

762
00:53:37,215 --> 00:53:39,342
He's looking for you.
Get up there and see him.

763
00:53:39,426 --> 00:53:41,845
- He wanted me?
- Yeah. Your name's Rock, right?

764
00:53:41,928 --> 00:53:43,847
- Yeah.
- All right. Go on, babe.

765
00:53:58,153 --> 00:53:59,988
You got something for me?

766
00:54:00,071 --> 00:54:02,908
Yeah, there was some guy
from Miles Jergens looking for you.

767
00:54:02,991 --> 00:54:06,494
They need sparring partners
for Apollo Creed. There's the card.

768
00:54:06,536 --> 00:54:08,246
- When was he here?
- About an hour ago.

769
00:54:08,330 --> 00:54:11,625
They're probably looking
for sparring partners for Creed.

770
00:54:11,666 --> 00:54:14,169
I said that before,
you dumb Dago!

771
00:54:15,670 --> 00:54:18,882
I been coming here for six years, and
six years you been sticking it to me.

772
00:54:18,965 --> 00:54:21,509
- How come?
- You don't wanna know!

773
00:54:21,551 --> 00:54:23,345
Yeah, I wanna know how come.

774
00:54:23,386 --> 00:54:25,430
- You wanna know?
- I wanna know now!

775
00:54:25,513 --> 00:54:27,557
Okay, I'm gonna tell you!

776
00:54:27,641 --> 00:54:31,686
You had the talent to become
a good fighter, and instead of that,

777
00:54:31,770 --> 00:54:35,899
you became a leg breaker
for some cheap, second-rate loan shark!

778
00:54:36,858 --> 00:54:38,026
It's a living.

779
00:54:38,068 --> 00:54:39,903
It's a waste of life!

780
00:54:58,505 --> 00:55:00,298
Yes. May I help you?

781
00:55:05,553 --> 00:55:08,098
Oh, you must be Mr. Rocky Balboa.

782
00:55:08,181 --> 00:55:11,059
Mr. Jergens's expecting you.
Just a moment.

783
00:55:16,189 --> 00:55:18,608
Mr. Rocky Balboa to see you, sir.

784
00:55:19,150 --> 00:55:20,276
Fine.

785
00:55:21,069 --> 00:55:23,571
- Please go in, Mr. Balboa.
- Can I have that?

786
00:55:23,613 --> 00:55:26,074
- Oh, certainly.
- Thanks.

787
00:55:30,829 --> 00:55:32,247
Mr. Balboa.

788
00:55:32,956 --> 00:55:34,749
How are you?
George Jergens.

789
00:55:34,833 --> 00:55:36,459
Take a chair, please.

790
00:55:36,543 --> 00:55:37,752
Thanks.

791
00:55:39,587 --> 00:55:41,006
Mr. Balboa.

792
00:55:41,589 --> 00:55:43,425
Call me Rocky.

793
00:55:43,508 --> 00:55:45,593
Rocky, you got any representation?

794
00:55:45,635 --> 00:55:47,137
You have a manager?

795
00:55:47,220 --> 00:55:48,638
No, just me.

796
00:55:50,265 --> 00:55:54,102
Rocky, I've got a proposition
I'd like to make to you.

797
00:55:54,519 --> 00:55:57,689
- About sparring?
- Beg your pardon?

798
00:55:57,772 --> 00:56:02,277
I know you're looking for sparring
partners, and I'm very available.

799
00:56:02,444 --> 00:56:04,279
- I'm sure you are.
- Absolutely.

800
00:56:04,362 --> 00:56:05,864
Sparring with the champ
would be an honor,

801
00:56:05,947 --> 00:56:07,198
and you know what, Mr. Jergens?

802
00:56:07,282 --> 00:56:09,159
- What?
- I wouldn't take no cheap shots.

803
00:56:09,242 --> 00:56:11,411
I'd really be a good
sparring partner.

804
00:56:11,453 --> 00:56:13,788
You don't understand me, Rocky.

805
00:56:14,205 --> 00:56:16,124
My proposition's this.

806
00:56:16,958 --> 00:56:19,335
Would you be interested
in fighting Apollo Creed

807
00:56:19,419 --> 00:56:22,130
for the world heavyweight
championship?

808
00:56:26,718 --> 00:56:27,802
No.

809
00:56:27,969 --> 00:56:29,512
Listen, Rocky.

810
00:56:30,472 --> 00:56:32,474
Apollo's seen you fight.

811
00:56:33,266 --> 00:56:34,893
He likes you.

812
00:56:34,976 --> 00:56:36,728
He wants to fight you.

813
00:56:36,811 --> 00:56:38,605
Well, it's just that, you see,

814
00:56:38,646 --> 00:56:41,816
I fight in clubs, you know,
and I'm really a ham-and-egger.

815
00:56:41,900 --> 00:56:43,777
This guy, he's the best, and

816
00:56:43,818 --> 00:56:47,489
it wouldn't be such a good fight,
but thank you very much.

817
00:56:47,989 --> 00:56:49,407
I appreciate it.

818
00:56:49,491 --> 00:56:53,828
Rocky, do you believe that America
is the land of opportunity?

819
00:56:55,330 --> 00:56:56,331
Yeah.

820
00:56:57,207 --> 00:56:58,917
Apollo Creed does,

821
00:56:59,292 --> 00:57:01,252
and he's gonna prove
it to the whole world

822
00:57:01,336 --> 00:57:04,047
by giving an unknown
a shot at the title.

823
00:57:04,547 --> 00:57:06,549
And that unknown is you.

824
00:57:07,300 --> 00:57:09,135
He picked you, Rocky.

825
00:57:10,345 --> 00:57:12,597
It's the chance of a lifetime.

826
00:57:13,723 --> 00:57:15,683
You can't pass it by.

827
00:57:16,851 --> 00:57:17,852
What do you say?

828
00:57:23,358 --> 00:57:25,527
<i>All right, fellas.
That's enough pictures.</i>

829
00:57:25,610 --> 00:57:27,487
<i>We wanna ask Apollo a few questions.</i>

830
00:57:27,529 --> 00:57:30,073
<i>Apollo, how do you like
the City of Brotherly Love?</i>

831
00:57:30,156 --> 00:57:33,576
<i>Well, just being in
Philadelphia makes me feel patriotic.</i>

832
00:57:33,660 --> 00:57:36,371
<i>Beautiful people in a beautiful city
coming up to me on the street,</i>

833
00:57:36,454 --> 00:57:37,664
<i>wishing me the best.</i>

834
00:57:37,705 --> 00:57:40,500
<i>I love my Philadelphia brothers,
and I'm proud to be an American.</i>

835
00:57:40,542 --> 00:57:42,085
<i>Apollo? Champ?</i>

836
00:57:42,168 --> 00:57:46,047
<i>Why did you agree to fight a man
who has virtually no chance of winning?</i>

837
00:57:46,089 --> 00:57:48,383
<i>If history proves one thing,</i>

838
00:57:48,466 --> 00:57:52,220
<i>American history proves that</i>
<i>everybody's got</i> a <i>chance to win.</i>

839
00:57:52,303 --> 00:57:55,431
<i>Didn't you guys ever hear
of Valley Forge or Bunker Hill?</i>

840
00:57:55,515 --> 00:57:57,058
<i>Apollo?</i>

841
00:57:57,100 --> 00:57:59,686
<i>It is a coincidence
that you're fighting a white man</i>

842
00:57:59,727 --> 00:58:01,729
<i>on the most celebrated day
in the country's history?</i>

843
00:58:01,771 --> 00:58:05,024
<i>I don't know. Is it a coincidence
that he's fighting a black man</i>

844
00:58:05,066 --> 00:58:07,402
<i>on the most celebrated day
in the country's history?</i>

845
00:58:07,485 --> 00:58:09,487
<i>- Right on, Apollo!
- Tell the truth, brother!</i>

846
00:58:09,571 --> 00:58:12,157
<i>Listen, Apollo. How
do you feel about your challenger?</i>

847
00:58:12,240 --> 00:58:14,993
<i>How do I feel about him?
Come here, Rock.</i>

848
00:58:15,451 --> 00:58:16,786
<i>My main man.</i>

849
00:58:16,870 --> 00:58:19,581
<i>- Rocky, ain't you Italian?
- Yeah, I'm Italian.</i>

850
00:58:19,622 --> 00:58:21,374
<i>Now what does that mean?</i>

851
00:58:21,416 --> 00:58:24,294
<i>That means, if he can't fight,
I'll bet he can cook.</i>

852
00:58:26,004 --> 00:58:28,590
Do me a favor. His lungs, punch out.

853
00:58:28,631 --> 00:58:30,091
Paulie.

854
00:58:30,133 --> 00:58:33,386
<i>Rocky, how do you expect
to fight Apollo Creed?</i>

855
00:58:33,928 --> 00:58:36,139
<i>Oh, jeez, you know,
Creed's the best.</i>

856
00:58:36,222 --> 00:58:37,932
<i>I guess I'll have to do
the best I can.</i>

857
00:58:37,974 --> 00:58:40,643
<i>Tell me, Rocky, just between us,</i>

858
00:58:40,727 --> 00:58:43,771
<i>where did you get
the name "Italian Stallion"?</i>

859
00:58:43,855 --> 00:58:48,276
<i>Oh, I invented that about eight
years ago when I was eating dinner.</i>

860
00:58:48,359 --> 00:58:53,156
<i>Rocky, now your payday
will be $150, 000.</i>

861
00:58:53,281 --> 00:58:54,699
<i>Any comment?</i>

862
00:58:56,951 --> 00:58:59,829
<i>- You got no comment, Rocky, right?
- No.</i>

863
00:58:59,913 --> 00:59:01,372
<i>- Thank you, Rocky.
- Wait a minute.</i>

864
00:59:01,456 --> 00:59:04,375
<i>I just wanna say hi to
my girlfriend, okay?</i>

865
00:59:04,459 --> 00:59:06,586
<i>Yo, Adrian, it's me, Rocky.</i>

866
00:59:07,670 --> 00:59:10,465
<i>You believe all this?
Microphones and all that stuff.</i>

867
00:59:10,506 --> 00:59:11,633
You didn't.

868
00:59:11,716 --> 00:59:14,052
<i>- Thank you, Rocky.
- Who you pushing, man?</i>

869
00:59:14,135 --> 00:59:16,471
<i>- Smack you in the mouth!
- Thank you, Rocky.</i>

870
00:59:16,554 --> 00:59:18,473
Don't it matter he making
you out a fool?

871
00:59:18,514 --> 00:59:20,141
I'd break his lips.

872
00:59:20,266 --> 00:59:23,853
- He's taking cheap shots.
- Don't bother me none.

873
00:59:23,937 --> 00:59:28,775
Yo, Rocky, I guess you'll be looking
for people to help you out.

874
00:59:28,816 --> 00:59:30,151
Help what?

875
00:59:30,193 --> 00:59:31,444
You know,

876
00:59:31,486 --> 00:59:33,446
keep you living the clean life.

877
00:59:33,488 --> 00:59:35,782
I do okay, you know.

878
00:59:35,823 --> 00:59:37,825
You need someone
to help with the exercise

879
00:59:37,867 --> 00:59:41,746
and someone standing by with a towel
or running errands?

880
00:59:41,829 --> 00:59:44,582
Hey, yo, Paulie,
who cared about me yesterday? Nobody.

881
00:59:44,666 --> 00:59:47,252
So I just think I'm gonna
train myself, you know?

882
00:59:47,335 --> 00:59:49,504
Without such good people around
to help you,

883
00:59:49,545 --> 00:59:52,006
you don't have such a good chance.

884
00:59:52,173 --> 00:59:54,717
Einstein flunked out
of school twice.

885
00:59:55,051 --> 00:59:56,302
That so?

886
00:59:56,469 --> 01:00:00,348
Yeah. Beethoven was deaf.
Helen Keller was blind.

887
01:00:00,890 --> 01:00:03,351
I think Rocky's got a good chance.

888
01:00:09,023 --> 01:00:11,150
Want me to get you a beer, Paulie?

889
01:00:11,192 --> 01:00:14,988
You looking to do a good deed?
Keep out of my freaking life!

890
01:00:15,863 --> 01:00:17,740
- What'd I do?
- Nothing.

891
01:00:17,824 --> 01:00:19,409
Did I say something wrong?

892
01:00:19,492 --> 01:00:21,244
You didn't say nothing.
It's all right.

893
01:00:21,327 --> 01:00:23,371
That's right!
You didn't say nothing!

894
01:00:23,413 --> 01:00:24,998
Nothing at all!

895
01:00:27,000 --> 01:00:28,376
I gotta go.

896
01:00:29,544 --> 01:00:31,921
Where are the freaking pretzels?

897
01:00:35,008 --> 01:00:36,926
I'd like to have a pretzel.

898
01:00:37,010 --> 01:00:39,137
Hey, we ain't got any beer?

899
01:00:40,013 --> 01:00:43,182
I thought you were supposed to
pick up some beer!

900
01:00:51,024 --> 01:00:53,609
How'd you like hearing your name
on TV tonight?

901
01:00:55,403 --> 01:00:56,904
I was shocked.

902
01:00:56,946 --> 01:00:58,406
Why'd you do that?

903
01:00:58,448 --> 01:01:00,241
You're putting me on, right?

904
01:01:00,283 --> 01:01:01,701
Absolutely.

905
01:01:02,452 --> 01:01:05,246
- What time should I expect you?
- About 7:00.

906
01:01:05,288 --> 01:01:07,248
- Okay.
- Hey.

907
01:01:24,766 --> 01:01:28,227
You know how I said
that stuff on TV didn't bother me?

908
01:01:28,603 --> 01:01:29,604
Yeah.

909
01:01:32,231 --> 01:01:33,483
It did.

910
01:01:44,118 --> 01:01:47,747
Listen, the reason I brought
you here is because

911
01:01:47,789 --> 01:01:50,124
I wanna know if you got any money
for training expenses.

912
01:01:50,208 --> 01:01:51,959
I got a few dollars.

913
01:01:52,043 --> 01:01:54,295
A few bucks? Here.
Put this in your glove.

914
01:01:54,379 --> 01:01:57,465
- What's this?
- $500. Don't worry about it.

915
01:01:58,674 --> 01:02:00,635
You know, you ain't
never had any luck,

916
01:02:00,676 --> 01:02:03,179
but I think this time Lady Luck
may be in your corner.

917
01:02:03,262 --> 01:02:06,224
- What do you think?
- Maybe.

918
01:02:06,307 --> 01:02:08,226
Thanks for the money, Tony.

919
01:02:08,309 --> 01:02:11,396
It's okay. Don't worry about it.
I'll see you.

920
01:02:11,646 --> 01:02:13,481
- Wait a minute.
- What?

921
01:02:13,523 --> 01:02:15,650
You're in training.
Come on.

922
01:02:23,825 --> 01:02:25,451
- Yo, Tony.
- What?

923
01:02:26,327 --> 01:02:28,579
You gonna show up at the fight?

924
01:02:28,663 --> 01:02:29,956
Ringside.

925
01:02:32,333 --> 01:02:33,835
I'll see you.

926
01:03:09,120 --> 01:03:10,121
Yeah.

927
01:03:15,710 --> 01:03:19,213
Hello, kid. I seen your light.
Can I come in?

928
01:03:19,297 --> 01:03:21,591
- Yeah, sure.
- Yeah. Good.

929
01:03:21,674 --> 01:03:23,801
Hey, it's a nice place here.

930
01:03:24,594 --> 01:03:27,388
Anyway, what I come
to tell you is that,

931
01:03:28,764 --> 01:03:32,059
that what happened to
you is freak luck.

932
01:03:32,101 --> 01:03:34,061
- Yeah, freak luck.
- Ain't it true?

933
01:03:34,103 --> 01:03:36,647
Look at the other guys.
They're good fighters, right?

934
01:03:36,731 --> 01:03:39,400
They're colorful.
They got good records.

935
01:03:39,484 --> 01:03:41,819
They fight their guts
out for peanuts.

936
01:03:41,903 --> 01:03:45,865
But you, you got
a shot at the title!

937
01:03:45,907 --> 01:03:48,409
Freak luck is a strange thing,
you know?

938
01:03:48,451 --> 01:03:50,995
- Sure is. Can I sit down?
- Yeah, sure.

939
01:03:52,580 --> 01:03:55,708
- What the hell are those?
- Domestic turtles.

940
01:03:55,750 --> 01:03:58,294
The one on the top is Cuff
and the other guy's Link.

941
01:03:58,377 --> 01:03:59,587
The rest are marbles.

942
01:03:59,670 --> 01:04:02,048
Yeah?
They make good soup.

943
01:04:02,757 --> 01:04:03,925
Anyway.

944
01:04:04,008 --> 01:04:06,928
Look, I'm here to warn you.

945
01:04:06,969 --> 01:04:11,516
You gotta be very careful about this
shot that you got at the title.

946
01:04:11,599 --> 01:04:14,393
Because, like the Bible says,

947
01:04:14,435 --> 01:04:16,604
you ain't gonna get a second chance.

948
01:04:16,687 --> 01:04:18,814
Yeah. All right.

949
01:04:18,898 --> 01:04:20,816
You thought of that, huh?

950
01:04:20,900 --> 01:04:24,320
Well, what you need is a manager.

951
01:04:25,279 --> 01:04:27,365
A manager. Listen to me.

952
01:04:27,448 --> 01:04:31,160
I know, because I been
in this racket for 50 years.

953
01:04:31,244 --> 01:04:34,539
- 50 years, huh?
- 50 years. I've seen it all.

954
01:04:34,622 --> 01:04:37,959
- All of it. You know what I done?
- What?

955
01:04:38,000 --> 01:04:40,002
I have done it all.

956
01:04:40,086 --> 01:04:43,881
You should've seen me when I knocked
Ginny Russell out of the ring.

957
01:04:43,965 --> 01:04:45,883
Out of the goddamn ring, I tell you.

958
01:04:45,967 --> 01:04:47,969
September 14, 1923,

